        </span></p></header><div><h2 id="introduction" class="test_h2 markdown-h2"><span>Introduction</span><a class="icon icon--link hash-link" href="#introduction" aria-label="Introduction"><img src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/btdevdoc/bundles/4.3.24/_assets/anchor-PKYVW2VT.svg" alt="AnchorIcon"/></a></h2><p class="markdown-p"><span>
            The
            </span><a href="/braintree/in-person/hardware/verifone-v400m/"><span>V400m reader</span></a><span>
            has a built-in receipt printer which can be triggered by using the receipt
            printing API's
            </span><a href="/braintree/graphql/reference/#Mutation--requestPrintFromInStoreReader"><code><span>requestPrintFromInStoreReader</span></code></a><span>
            mutation discussed on this page. The receipt printing API allows for an
            API caller to fully customize the text, line items, images, and other
            information printed on the V400m built-in receipt printer. The total
            contents on a given receipt printing request cannot exceed 122,880 bytes
            in size, giving the API caller ample room for a fully customized receipt.
        </span></p><h2 id="initiating-a-printing-request" class="test_h2 markdown-h2"><span>Initiating a printing request</span><a class="icon icon--link hash-link" href="#initiating-a-printing-request" aria-label="Initiating a printing request"><img src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/btdevdoc/bundles/4.3.24/_assets/anchor-PKYVW2VT.svg" alt="AnchorIcon"/></a></h2><p class="markdown-p"><span>
            To initiate a printing request using the
            </span><a href="/braintree/graphql/reference/#Mutation--requestPrintFromInStoreReader"><code><span>requestPrintFromInStoreReader</span></code></a><span>
            API mutation you must specify a
            </span><code><span>readerId</span></code><span>
            for the V400m device you want to print from and the
            </span><a href="/braintree/graphql/reference/#Input--RequestPrintFromInStoreReaderInput"><code><span>contents</span></code></a><span>
            that you would like to print on the receipt. For the request to be
            successful there must be a minimum of 1 content and a maximum of 500
            contents in the request. Each content represents a text line or an image
            to be printed on the receipt. The
            </span><code><span>contents</span></code><span>
            for any given receipt request cannot exceed 122,880 bytes in size. Within
            the
            </span><code><span>contents</span></code><span>
            you must specify the
            </span><a href="/braintree/graphql/reference/#Input--InStorePrintContentInput"><span>type of input</span></a><span>
            being either a text or an image.
        </span></p><h3 id="text-inputs" class="test_h3 markdown-h3"><span>Text Inputs</span><a class="icon icon--link hash-link" href="#text-inputs" aria-label="Text Inputs"><img src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/btdevdoc/bundles/4.3.24/_assets/anchor-PKYVW2VT.svg" alt="AnchorIcon"/></a></h3><p class="markdown-p"><span>
            When using the
            </span><a href="/braintree/graphql/reference/#Input--InStorePrintTextInput"><span>text input</span></a><span>
            to write a text line on the receipt you may specify the text
            </span><code><span>value</span></code><span>
            which is the actual text being printed, the
            </span><code><span>alignment</span></code><span>
            of the text, and the
            </span><code><span>endOfLineFlag</span></code><span>
            to determine when a given text line should be ended to start a new line
            with your next
            </span><code><span>content</span></code><span>. The default styling will apply to the text unless
            you also specify the
            </span><code><span>textDecoration</span></code><span>
            which controls the emphasis on the text, the
            </span><code><span>fontWeight</span></code><span>, the </span><code><span>fontStyle</span></code><span>, and the
            </span><code><span>fontSize</span></code><span>.
        </span></p><h3 id="image-inputs" class="test_h3 markdown-h3"><span>Image Inputs</span><a class="icon icon--link hash-link" href="#image-inputs" aria-label="Image Inputs"><img src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/btdevdoc/bundles/4.3.24/_assets/anchor-PKYVW2VT.svg" alt="AnchorIcon"/></a></h3><p class="markdown-p"><span>
            When using the
            </span><a href="/braintree/graphql/reference/#Input--InStorePrintImageInput"><span>image input</span></a><span>
            to print images such as business logos or QR codes the image must be in a
            PNG image format and cannot exceed 76,800 bytes in size. The PNG image
            must also be base64 encoded before passing the base64 encoded string in
            the
            </span><code><span>value</span></code><span>
            API field. You may also specify the
            </span><code><span>endOfLineFlag</span></code><span>
            to determine when the next text line or image line should begin, as well
            as the
            </span><code><span>alignment</span></code><span>
            of the image to be printed. For optimization, the ideal image width is 300
            pixels.
        </span></p><h3 id="example-print-request" class="test_h3 markdown-h3"><span>Example print request</span><a class="icon icon--link hash-link" href="#example-print-request" aria-label="Example print request"><img src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/btdevdoc/bundles/4.3.24/_assets/anchor-PKYVW2VT.svg" alt="AnchorIcon"/></a></h3><div class="styles_tab_container"><ol class="styles_tab_list"><div><li class="styles_tab_list_item styles_tab_list_active">GraphQL Mutation</li><li class="styles_tab_list_item">GraphQL Variables</li><li class="styles_tab_list_item">Sample API Response</li></div></ol><div class="codeblock-spacing"><button class="copy-button" aria-label="Copy"><span class="copy-status">Copy</span><svg class="snippet__copy-icon" fill="#ffffff" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none"></path><path d="M16 1H4c-1.1 0-2 .9-2 2v14h2V3h12V1zm3 4H8c-1.1 0-2 .9-2 2v14c0 1.1.9 2 2 2h11c1.1 0 2-.9 2-2V7c0-1.1-.9-2-2-2zm0 16H8V7h11v14z"></path></svg></button><pre><code class="javascript">mutation RequestPrintFromInStoreReader($input: RequestPrintFromInStoreReaderInput!) {
              requestPrintFromInStoreReader(input: $input) {
                  clientMutationId
                  id
                  reader {
                      id
                      name
                      status
                      location {
                          id
                          name
                          address {
                              streetAddress
                              extendedAddress
                              locality
                              region
                              postalCode
                              countryCode
                          }
                      }
                  }
                  status
              }
          }</code></pre></div></div><p class="markdown-p"><span>
            Once you make the initial request you must also begin a context ID polling
            process so that your application can determine whether the printing action
            was successful or not.
        </span></p><h3 id="example-context-id-polling-request" class="test_h3 markdown-h3"><span>Example context ID polling request</span><a class="icon icon--link hash-link" href="#example-context-id-polling-request" aria-label="Example context ID polling request"><img src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/btdevdoc/bundles/4.3.24/_assets/anchor-PKYVW2VT.svg" alt="AnchorIcon"/></a></h3><p class="markdown-p"><span>
            We recommend polling every 1-2 seconds to get the final result. There is a
            default timeout of 30 seconds if the print is unsuccessful. Follow our
            general
            </span><a href="/braintree/in-person/guides/making-a-transaction/#checking-the-reader-charge-status"><span>node query polling logic</span></a><span>
            documented in our payment processing documentation.
        </span></p><div class="styles_tab_container"><ol class="styles_tab_list"><div><li class="styles_tab_list_item styles_tab_list_active">GraphQL Mutation</li><li class="styles_tab_list_item">GraphQL Variables</li><li class="styles_tab_list_item">Sample API Response</li></div></ol><div class="codeblock-spacing"><button class="copy-button" aria-label="Copy"><span class="copy-status">Copy</span><svg class="snippet__copy-icon" fill="#ffffff" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M0 0h24v24H0z" fill="none"></path><path d="M16 1H4c-1.1 0-2 .9-2 2v14h2V3h12V1zm3 4H8c-1.1 0-2 .9-2 2v14c0 1.1.9 2 2 2h11c1.1 0 2-.9 2-2V7c0-1.1-.9-2-2-2zm0 16H8V7h11v14z"></path></svg></button><pre><code class="javascript">query ID($contextId: ID!) {
          node(id: $contextId) {
            ... on RequestPrintInStoreContext {
                __typename
                id
                status
                errors {
                    message
                    errorCode
                }
            }
          }
        }</code></pre></div></div><h2 id="printing-receipts-in-offline-mode" class="test_h2 markdown-h2"><span>Printing Receipts in Offline Mode</span><a class="icon icon--link hash-link" href="#printing-receipts-in-offline-mode" aria-label="Printing Receipts in Offline Mode"><img src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/btdevdoc/bundles/4.3.24/_assets/anchor-PKYVW2VT.svg" alt="AnchorIcon"/></a></h2><p class="markdown-p"><span>
            If you are implementing the
            </span><a href="/braintree/in-person/guides/offline-transactions/"><span>offline processing</span></a><span>

        </span></p><div><div><img src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/devdoc/btdocs-gitbook/Receipt%20Printing%20API-Sample%20Receipt%20Template.png"/></div></div><p class="markdown-p"><span>

Receipt Printing API\nslug: /in-person/guides/receipt-printing-api/\ncreateTime: '2024-11-20T19:01:48.914Z'\nupdateTime: '2025-01-03T22:01:36.034Z'\n---\n\n\n\n# Receipt Printing API\n\nThis documentation article discusses the Receipt Printing API which is available for the V400m device only\n\n\n## Introduction\n\nThe [V400m reader](/braintree/in-person/hardware/verifone-v400m/) has a built-in receipt printer which can be triggered by using the receipt printing API's [requestPrintFromInStoreReader](/braintree/graphql/reference/#Mutation--requestPrintFromInStoreReader) mutation discussed on this page. The receipt printing API allows for an API caller to fully customize the text, line items, images, and other information printed on the V400m built-in receipt printer. The total contents on a given receipt printing request cannot exceed 122,880 bytes in size, giving the API caller ample room for a fully customized receipt.\n\n\n## Initiating a printing request\n\nTo initiate a printing request using the [requestPrintFromInStoreReader](/braintree/graphql/reference/#Mutation--requestPrintFromInStoreReader) API mutation you must specify a readerId for the V400m device you want to print from and the [contents](/braintree/graphql/reference/#Input--RequestPrintFromInStoreReaderInput) that you would like to print on the receipt. For the request to be successful there must be a minimum of 1 content and a maximum of 500 contents in the request. Each content represents a text line or an image to be printed on the receipt. The contents for any given receipt request cannot exceed 122,880 bytes in size. Within the contents you must specify the [type of input](/braintree/graphql/reference/#Input--InStorePrintContentInput) being either a text or an image.\n\n\n### Text Inputs\n\nWhen using the [text input](/braintree/graphql/reference/#Input--InStorePrintTextInput) to write a text line on the receipt you may specify the text value which is the actual text being printed, the alignment of the text, and the endOfLineFlag to determine when a given text line should be ended to start a new line with your next content. The default styling will apply to the text unless you also specify the textDecoration which controls the emphasis on the text, the fontWeight, the fontStyle, and the fontSize.\n\n\n### Image Inputs\n\nWhen using the [image input](/braintree/graphql/reference/#Input--InStorePrintImageInput) to print images such as business logos or QR codes the image must be in a PNG image format and cannot exceed 76,800 bytes in size. The PNG image must also be base64 encoded before passing the base64 encoded string in the value API field. You may also specify the endOfLineFlag to determine when the next text line or image line should begin, as well as the alignment of the image to be printed. For optimization, the ideal image width is 300 pixels.\n\n\n### Example print request\n\nGraphQL MutationGraphQL VariablesSample API Responsemutation RequestPrintFromInStoreReader($input: RequestPrintFromInStoreReaderInput!) { requestPrintFromInStoreReader(input: $input) { clientMutationId id reader { id name status location { id name address { streetAddress extendedAddress locality region postalCode countryCode } } } status } }{ \"input\": { \"readerId\": \"input your reader ID\", \"contents\": [ { \"image\": { \"value\": \"\", \"alignment\": \"CENTER\" } }, { \"text\": { \"value\": \"LEFT_TEXT\", \"alignment\": \"LEFT\", \"fontWeight\": \"BOLD\", \"fontSize\": 20, \"endOfLineFlag\": false } }, { \"text\": { \"value\": \"RIGHT_TEXT\", \"alignment\": \"RIGHT\", \"textDecoration\": \"UNDERLINE\", \"fontStyle\": \"ITALIC\", \"fontSize\": 24 } } ] } }{ \"data\": { \"requestPrintFromInStoreReader\": { \"clientMutationId\": null, \"id\": \"aW5zdG9yZWNvbnRleHRfIJhYzJiODQxYjU5YzdmODc2MDc0YTQ4ZTM0I1ZFUklGT05FLTQ1Mi05OTYtMDY1I3VzLXdlc3QtMg\", \"reader\": { \"id\": \"aW5zdG9yZXJlY0ZWdyYXRpb25fbWVyY2hhbnRfaWQjVkVSSUZPTkUtNDUyLTk5Ni0wNjU\", \"name\": \"Register 1 V400m\", \"status\": \"ONLINE\", \"location\": { \"id\": \"aW5zdG9yZWxvY2F0aWYxOWM4OC00OTEwLTQ4ZTMtYjhmMS01MDY5NjZiOWVjN2U\", \"name\": \"Retail Shop PP\", \"address\": { \"streetAddress\": \"18 West Side Avenue\", \"extendedAddress\": \"Unit b\", \"locality\": \"Beverly Hills\", \"region\": \"California\", \"postalCode\": \"90210\", \"countryCode\": \"USA\" } } }, \"status\": \"PENDING\" } }, \"extensions\": { \"requestId\": \"02063e92-5e2d-45ab-8757-fcd98e9fecbf\" } }Once you make the initial request you must also begin a context ID polling process so that your application can determine whether the printing action was successful or not.\n\n\n### Example context ID polling request\n\nWe recommend polling every 1-2 seconds to get the final result.
